An up-rising Nollywood actor, Taiwo Adeyemi, has labelled Nollywood lovers as ‘extremists’. The rising actor made the statement while reacting to the level of criticism the movie industry receives from viewers in the country. The actor, however, compared Nollywood to Hollywood, saying the American Hollywood has its challenges but the criticism is not as extreme as it is with Nollywood in Nigeria. Taiwo Adeyemi, who has featured in several movies, decried the chances given to up-coming actors by filmmakers in the movie industry. ‘The Slave Driver’ movie: a campaign against divorce Ayo Mogaji of “Feyikogbon” down with kidney… Kogi guber: APC stakeholders hail Adeyemi’s… Reality star Alex Unusual makes Nollywood debut in ‘Merry… He added that his passion for acting has made him relevant in Nollywood, saying the movie industry has always been a big challenge to rising actors. ALSO READ: FG to inaugurate committee on fake news, hate speech Speaking further, he said Nollywood industry would extra miles to achieve its desire, saying some producers do not care about the use of cameras and other equipment in film-making. “There is so much competition in the industry and it’s super great. Everyone is on their toes working earnestly, even the celebrity actors and actresses never stopped improving daily,” he submitted. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE. PREMATURE EJACULATION, SMALL SIZE FINALLY CURED NATURALLY IN 2 WEEKS FOR BIGGER, LONGER, HARDER SEXIER SEX WITH NAFDAC APPROVED JAMES BOND.